text: One of the better chicken rice around the area. Their roasted chicken sells out really fast. Uncle was very friendly and portion offered always good. They have double boiled soups on their menu as well. The family had tried their food and they were good by general standard. The stall is located right at the corner of the coffee shop. Prices are economical and reasonable.

Xing Le Xing chicken rice is a hidden gem in Singapore's culinary scene. The succulent chicken, paired with fragrant rice and a delightful homemade chili, rivals renowned establishments like Boon Tong Kee and Tian Tian Hainanese Chicken Rice. This culinary experience deserves a solid 5/5, proving that great flavors can be found beyond the expected favorites.
The young big guy is dishonest.  He overcharged and refused to admit.  $7 a drumstick without rice when it is stated $5.50 a drumstick with rice.
One of the better chicken rice stalls around the area. Both steamed and roasted are good.
